      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum nonlinear FEA with frictional contact and bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity is appropriate for the compression-bending regime of interest.",
      "rationale": "The model employs 3-D continuum elements with frictional Coulomb contact at screw-rod and rod-saddle interfaces, and bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V. Large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM ON) are activated. This model form is consistent with published literature on pedicle screw FEA and captures the dominant failure mechanisms observed in testing. Required level 3 achieved."
